Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

This page gives you guidance on how to stay safely in Angola as a visitor, if you are unable to return to the UK.
Everyone should comply with the measures put in place in Angola to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
Moving around in Angola
The current State of Emergency has been extended until at least 25 May. This includes a series of measures to limit the spread of the virus, including:
Significant restrictions on movement throughout the country. All citizens to remain at home, but specified exemptions for some workers, essential shopping and medical treatment.
Closure of most shops, other than those selling food or medicine which are operating reduced hours.
Reduced public transport and suspension of domestic flights via the capital.
The Angolan police are robustly enforcing these rules. You should continue to comply with any additional measures put in place by the local authorities.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
